nce >= 0.8\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: Valine\nOVERALL STRATEGY: This network generates valine through three independent terminal routes\u2014Strecker synthesis, reductive amination, and transamination\u2014all converging from prebiotically plausible C1-C4 building blocks. The strategy avoids the speculative acetolactate pathway entirely, instead using Varma et al.-type reductive carboxylation of isobutyraldehyde to generate \u03b1-ketoisovalerate. Hydrothermal environments produce C1 species (CO, formate, formaldehyde) and small aldehydes (acetaldehyde, propanal) via Fischer-Tropsch-type chemistry on mineral catalysts. Surface environments drive aldol condensation, HCN synthesis, and Strecker chemistry. Biochemical environments enable transamination and final macromolecular-level assembly. Hub molecules (formaldehyde, HCN, isobutyraldehyde, \u03b1-ketoisovalerate, pyruvate) create genuine convergence points where multiple independent routes intersect, providing redundancy and robustness.\n\nMOLECULES (19 nodes):\n  - mol_001: CO2 (carbon dioxide) [starting]\n  - mol_002: H2 (hydrogen gas) [starting]\n  - mol_003: NH3 (ammonia) [starting]\n  - mol_004: H2O (water) [starting]\n  - mol_005: CO (carbon monoxide) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_006: CHOO- (formate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_007: CH2O (formaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_008: HCN (hydrogen cyanide) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_009: C2H4O (acetaldehyde) [intermediate]\n  - mol_010: C3H6O (propanal) [intermediate]\n  - mol_011: C4H8O (isobutyraldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_012: C5H10N2 (alpha-aminoisovaleronitrile) [intermediate]\n  - mol_013: C3H3O3- (pyruvate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_014: C5H7O3- (alpha-ketoisovalerate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_015: C3H7NO2 (alanine) [intermediate]\n  - mol_016: C4H6O (methacrolein) [intermediate]\n  - mol_017: C5H11NO2 (valine) [target]\n  - mol_018: C2H5NO2 (glycine) [intermediate]\n  - mol_019: C4H7NO (isobutyraldehyde cyanohydrin) [intermediate]\n\nREACTIONS (21 nodes):\n  - rxn_001: mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_005, mol_004 (CO\u2082 reduction to CO via reverse water-gas shift on magnetite) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_002: mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_006 (CO\u2082 reduction to formate on greigite) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_003: mol_005, mol_002 -> mol_007 (Fischer-Tropsch-type formaldehyde synthesis from CO) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_004: mol_006, mol_002 -> mol_007 (Formate reduction to formaldehyde on native iron) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_005: mol_005, mol_002 -> mol_009, mol_010 (Fischer-Tropsch-type synthesis of C2-C3 aldehydes) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_006: mol_003, mol_007 -> mol_008, mol_004 (Photochemical HCN synthesis from NH\u2083 and formaldehyde) [Surface]\n  - rxn_007: mol_010, mol_007 -> mol_016 (Cross-aldol condensation of propanal with formaldehyde) [Surface]\n  - rxn_008: mol_016, mol_002 -> mol_011 (Reduction of methacrolein to isobutyraldehyde on pyrite) [Surface]\n  - rxn_009: mol_005, mol_002 -> mol_011 (Direct FTT synthesis of isobutyraldehyde) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_010: mol_011, mol_008, mol_003 -> mol_012 (Strecker synthesis step 1: aminonitrile formation from isobutyraldehyde) [Surface]\n  - rxn_011: mol_012, mol_004 -> mol_017 (Strecker synthesis step 2: hydrolysis of aminonitrile to valine) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_012: mol_009, mol_001 -> mol_013 (Reductive carboxylation of acetaldehyde to pyruvate on native iron) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_013: mol_011, mol_001 -> mol_014 (Reductive carboxylation of isobutyraldehyde to \u03b1-ketoisovalerate on native iron) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_014: mol_014, mol_003, mol_002 -> mol_017 (Reductive amination of \u03b1-ketoisovalerate to valine on greigite) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_015: mol_013, mol_003, mol_002 -> mol_015 (Reductive amination of pyruvate to alanine on greigite) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_016: mol_014, mol_015 -> mol_017, mol_013 (Transamination of \u03b1-ketoisovalerate with alanine to form valine) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_017: mol_007, mol_008, mol_003 -> mol_018 (Strecker synthesis of glycine from formaldehyde) [Surface]\n  - rxn_018: mol_014, mol_018 -> mol_017 (Transamination of \u03b1-ketoisovalerate with glycine to form valine) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_019: mol_011, mol_008 -> mol_019 (Cyanohydrin formation from isobutyraldehyde with HCN) [Surface]\n  - rxn_020: mol_019, mol_003, mol_004 -> mol_017 (Cyanohydrin ammonolysis and hydrolysis to valine) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_021: mol_013 -> mol_009, mol_001 (Thermal decarboxylation of pyruvate to acetaldehyde) [Surface]\n\nPATHWAYS (10):\n  - P1: Primary Strecker via aldol-derived isobutyraldehyde (7 steps)\n  - P2: Strecker via formate-derived formaldehyde and FTT propanal (8 steps)\n  - P3: Strecker via direct FTT isobutyraldehyde (5 steps)\n  - P4: Reductive amination via aldol isobutyraldehyde carboxylation (7 steps)\n  - P5: Reductive amination via direct FTT isobutyraldehyde carboxylation (4 steps)\n  - P6: Transamination with alanine via aldol route (9 steps)\n  - P7: Transamination with glycine (7 steps)\n  - P8: Cyanohydrin route to valine (8 steps)\n  - P9: Formate-formaldehyde-HCN integrated Strecker with FTT isobutyraldehyde (7 steps)\n  - P10: Pyruvate decarboxylation recycling with transamination (8 steps)\n\nHUB MOLECULES: mol_007, mol_008, mol_011, mol_014, mol_013\nCONVERGENCE POINTS: 5\n\n\nPlease evaluate the network and respond with JSON:\n{\n    \"pathway_evaluations\": [\n        {\n            \"pathway_id\": \"<id>\",\n            \"reaction_scores\": {\"rxn_001\": 0.85, ...},\n            \"chemical_feasibility\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"pathway_coherence\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"environmental_progression\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"target_achievement\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"overall_confidence\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"feedback\": \"<pathway-specific feedback>\",\n            \"approved\": <true if confidence >= 0.8>